Description: Two joining sherds of lower body of large North Ionian pottery dinos; inside reserved; exterior: broad band separates two much worn friezes; in lower frieze, goat to right, looking back; added red on haunch.
Curator's comments: Probably from same vessel as 1888,0601.393a-e & g-h
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 65, no. 784, pl. XXI, no. 784)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 685, no. 435)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1086)
